<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbba7a482-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s1962c–5"><num value="1962c–5">§ 1962c–5.</num><heading> “State” defined</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For the purpose of this subchapter the term “State” means a State, the District of Columbia, Puerto Rico, the Virgin Islands or Guam.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbba7a483-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/80/tIII/s306">Pub. L. 89–80, title III, § 306</ref>, <date date="1965-07-22">July 22, 1965</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/79/253">79 Stat. 253</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/94/285/s2">Pub. L. 94–285, § 2</ref>, <date date="1976-05-12">May 12, 1976</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/90/516">90 Stat. 516</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idbba7a484-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idbba7a485-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idbba7a486-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1976—<ref href="/us/pl/94/285">Pub. L. 94–285</ref> inserted reference to Guam.</p>
</note>
